com.gfycat.webp

Class WebPImage

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gfycat.webp.WebPImage

  • public class WebPImage
extends java.lang.Object
    A representation of a WebP image. An instance of this class will hold a copy of the encoded data in memory along with the parsed header data. Frames are decoded on demand via WebPFrame.

        public static WebPImage create(byte[] source)
        Creates a WebPImage from the specified encoded data. This will throw if it fails to create. This is meant to be called on a worker thread.
        Parameters:
        source - the data to the image (a copy will be made)
